snippet.textDisplay: Everyone complaining about going public ruining the secrecy of rainbow, but nowhere is it implied that the stadium is sponsored or backed by rainbow, or that all the operators are working under a single organization; all the audience knows is that the top operators from CTUs around the world have been selected to compete against one another in a single stadium with the goal of “coming together so that [they] may be stronger apart.”  Key word “apart”, which is to imply to the audience that the operators will eventually return to their respective CTUs and be apart from eacho their (obviously they actually won’t). If this is all that the audience knows, they are still in the dark about Team Rainbow’s existence.
